{
  "texts": [
    "As shown in the bottom part of Fig. 5, the 2DCNN expands 1DCNN to a 2-dimensional grid with considering the input of a 2-dimensional matrix form.",
    "If the original input is three dimensional, z ∈ ℝ T×P×N feat, where T is the length of time series, P is the number of wind turbines, and N feat is the number of features in each time step and wind turbine of input z, a common organization is to regard the time steps as different input channels, and the features of different wind turbines are organized as a matrix.",
    "The 3DCNN is typically used to extract spatial-temporal features from the 3-dimensional input z ∈ ℝ T×P×N feat.",
    "The definition of 3DCNN is similar to that of 1DCNN and that of 2DCNN.",
    "Page 29 of 49 112"
  ]
}